<p>President Trump said U.S. forces struck a small boat accused of carrying drugs in international waters off Venezuela on Tuesday, killing six people aboard and leaving no U.S. personnel harmed [theguardian.com#1][bbc.com#1][japantoday.com#1][cbsnews.com#1]. He described those on board as &quot;narcoterrorists&quot; and posted a video of the blast, while U.S. officials have not publicly provided evidence supporting the drug-trafficking claim [firstpost.com#1][thehindu.com#1][bbc.com#1]. The administration says intelligence tied the vessel to narcotics trafficking and known routes, and has framed alleged traffickers as unlawful combatants [lemonde.fr#1][scmp.com#1]. This was the fifth deadly strike in the Caribbean in recent weeks, bringing total reported deaths from these operations to 27, and it follows a narrow Senate defeat of an effort to curb the administration&#x27;s actions on legal grounds [cbsnews.com#1][elpais.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1]. The UN has condemned earlier small-boat strikes as extrajudicial executions, fueling international legal debate over the campaign [theguardian.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/1lLtHewBqCGaOfGx_5tE0Pa8VJKoNdSPSaihDYNvb2ZDqJLsjR0Otp_3KQxSUJJnZ-rVYsU_VXItB0lzATmfnSbf1bx_RzqyE7swkWhp7h_wGx_Ogrfp7WFDlo8iZDKdG0sIvzLp7g0e5eY5yqB8tsAC7mA-26AzjAOqWYXxo_F-pTceEO4zXUrXBG-HIfTZXBaQTqdcI9M4PQ680mhmq2JoxI090_EPBP9GC0mK9prESfEOMbfvc4KSnZfQ6zz5nKxIgMvV3L0' alt='Venezuelan coast guard patrols the Caribbean coast amid heightened U.S.-Venezuela tensions.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Fifth operation: This was the fifth deadly strike against a suspected drug-smuggling boat in the Caribbean in recent weeks [cbsnews.com#1][scmp.com#1][elpais.com#1].</li><li>Casualty count: A total of 27 people have died across these U.S. operations, including the six reported in the latest strike [elpais.com#1].</li><li>Legal scrutiny: The UN has condemned prior small-boat strikes as extrajudicial executions, and former U.S. military lawyers say the administration’s legal rationale falls short of law-of-war standards [theguardian.com#1][theglobeandmail.com#1].</li><li>Evidence status: Trump posted a surveillance video showing a projectile hitting a stationary vessel, but U.S. officials have not publicly provided evidence the boat carried drugs [firstpost.com#1][thehindu.com#1][bbc.com#1].</li><li>Political backdrop: The strike comes after Senate Republicans narrowly defeated a measure aiming to block the administration’s actions on legal grounds [washingtonpost.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>No U.S. Forces were harmed. - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. administration: Officials say intelligence confirmed the vessel was trafficking narcotics, associated with &#x27;narcoterrorist networks,&#x27; and on a known route. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/15/us-kills-6-people-in-strike-on-boat-accused-of-carrying-drugs-near-venezuela-trump-says_6746444_4.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li><li>U.S. administration: The administration has asserted it is treating alleged drug traffickers as unlawful combatants to be met with military force. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3329039/trump-says-us-strike-another-alleged-drug-boat-venezuela-kills-6'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>United Nations: UN officials condemned earlier small-boat strikes as extrajudicial executions. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/oct/14/trump-six-killed-us-strike-boat-venezuela'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Former U.S. military lawyers: They argue the administration’s legal explanations do not meet law-of-war requirements. (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-venezuela-boat-us-strike-drug-cartel-trump-maduro/'>The Globe and Mail</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/oct/14/trump-six-killed-us-strike-boat-venezuela'>Trump says six were killed in US strike on another 